---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Aroma de Cuba"
  description="Privacy policy for Aroma de Cuba. Information about how we collect, use and protect your data."
  lang="en"
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-10">Last updated: February 22, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none space-y-8">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Aroma de Cuba</strong> (<a href="https://aromadecuba.com" class="text-enchilado hover:underline">aromadecuba.com</a>) is an informational and cultural blog dedicated to Cuba — its history, gastronomy, culture, and news. The site is independently operated and does not collect personal data for commercial purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We do not directly collect personally identifiable information. However, when browsing this site, the following technical data may be collected automatically:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>IP address (anonymized)</li>
          <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
          <li>Referring page (referrer)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">This information is used exclusively to improve site performance and understand visitor behavior in aggregate form.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site may use essential technical cookies for its operation. We do not use tracking cookies or personalized advertising cookies. If you visit our pages through a social media link, those platforms may set their own cookies according to their policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Third Parties and Social Media</h2>
        <p>Aroma de Cuba has a presence on the following external platforms:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Facebook / Meta:</strong> We publish content on our Facebook page. If you interact with those posts, Meta collects data according to their own <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" class="text-enchilado hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>. We use the Facebook API to automatically publish articles on our page.</li>
          <li><strong>Vercel:</strong> The site is hosted on Vercel servers, which may log technical access data according to their privacy policy.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Facebook Data Usage</h2>
        <p>
          In the context of our Facebook (Meta) API integration, we use the following permissions: <code>pages_manage_posts</code>, <code>pages_read_engagement</code>, and <code>pages_show_list</code>. These permissions are used exclusively to publish blog articles on our Facebook page. We do not access or store personal data of Facebook users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. External Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our articles may contain links to third-party websites (news sources, government agencies, etc.). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites. We recommend reading their policies before providing personal information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Since we do not collect personally identifiable data, we have no data to delete or correct upon request. If you have any questions about the use of your data, you can contact us at:</p>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@aromadecuba.com" class="text-enchilado hover:underline">hello@aromadecuba.com</a></p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy occasionally. Changes will be posted on this page with the last updated date. We recommend reviewing it periodically.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>For any questions related to this privacy policy:</p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          <strong>Aroma de Cuba</strong><br />
          <a href="mailto:hello@aromadecuba.com" class="text-enchilado hover:underline">hello@aromadecuba.com</a><br />
          <a href="https://aromadecuba.com" class="text-enchilado hover:underline">aromadecuba.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-stone-200">
      <a href="/en/" class="text-sm text-enchilado hover:underline">← Back to home</a>
      <span class="mx-3 text-stone-300">|</span>
      <a href="/privacidad" class="text-sm text-enchilado hover:underline">Versión en español →</a>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
